<para>There are a few steps to get up and running on own system:</para>
<sect3 id="md__docs_2_getting_01_started_1autotoc_md3">
<title>1. Software dependencies</title>
<para><ulink url="https://conan.io/index.html">Conan</ulink></para>
<para>This is an open source, decentralized and multi-platform package manager for C/C++.</para>
<para>Recommended install:</para>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Install Python:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Windows: <ulink url="https://www.python.org/ftp/python/3.8.7/python-3.8.7-amd64.exe">Python 3.8.7.exe</ulink></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Linux: <computeroutput>$ sudo apt-get update</computeroutput> <computeroutput>$ sudo apt-get install python3.8</computeroutput></para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Install Conan:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Windows/Linux: <computeroutput>$ pip install conan</computeroutput></para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para><ulink url="https://cmake.org">CMake</ulink></para>
<para>CMake is a cross-platform, open-source build system generator.</para>
<para>Install CMake:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Windows: <ulink url="https://github.com/Kitware/CMake/releases/download/v3.19.3/cmake-3.19.3-win32-x86.msi">cmake-3.19.3-win64-x64.msi</ulink></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Linux: <ulink url="https://github.com/Kitware/CMake/releases/download/v3.19.3/cmake-3.19.3-Linux-x86_64.sh">cmake-3.19.3-Linux-x86_64.sh</ulink></para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="md__docs_2_getting_01_started_1autotoc_md4">
<title>2. Installation process</title>
</sect3>
