<title>Windows:</title>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="md__docs_2_getting_01_started_1autotoc_md6">
<title>Visual Studio 2019/2022:</title>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Clone this repository or download as Zip from Github.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Run Visual Studio and open this repository as folder. It will automatically detect the root CMakeLists.txt and execute it, after which you can start/debug the server and client sides.</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="md__docs_2_getting_01_started_1autotoc_md7">
<title>Linux:</title>
<para><bold>Visual Code</bold>:</para>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Clone this repository or download as Zip from Github.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Run VS Code and open the root CMakeLists.txt. It will automatically detect the root CMakeLists.txt and execute it, after which you can start/debug the server and client sides.</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
